</strong></span></p><p class="sc-bJBfJu eVDjFe pf-84_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bOQUxc quwHz pf-86_"><strong>Inclusion and adaptation are key elements for community clothing initiatives</strong>, allowing diverse groups within a community to feel heard and respected [11]. The satisfaction of being part of a community where shared values and interests align around external challenges, while maintaining harmony, is a powerful motivator [11].&nbsp;<strong><br>

